title: Woodside makes bid for Oil Search
text:
Tue, Sep 8, 2015, 11:21 AM AEST - Australia Markets close in 4 hrs 39 mins Woodside makes bid for Oil Search AAP – 45 minutes ago Print 
Energy giant Woodside Petroleum has made a non-binding proposal to acquire all shares in Papua New Guinea-focused oil and gas player Oil Search. 
Woodside, which has been keen to make acquisitions, has offered one Woodside share for every four shares in Oil Search in an all-scrip deal. 
The proposal would be subject to Papua New Guinea regulatory approval. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Hugh Jackman named as Qantas ambassador AAP
